<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Enter</title>
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="https://ajax.aspnetcdn.com/ajax/bootstrap/4.3.1/css/bootstrap.min.css">
	<script type="text/javascript" src="https://ajax.aspnetcdn.com/ajax/jQuery/jquery-3.4.1.min.js"></script>
	<script type="text/javascript" src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.3.1/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
	<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:300,400,700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

	<script type="text/javascript" src="/assets/js/enter.js"></script>
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/assets/css/enter.css">
</head>
<body>
	<div class="container-fluid">
		<div class="row no-gutter enter">
			<div class="d-md-flex col-md-4 col-lg-6 bg-image">
				<div class="d-flex align-items-center" style="height: 100%; width: 100%;">
					<div class="title-div">
						<h1 class="title">One Reading Club</h1>
						<p class="title" style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Expanding Our Horizons Together</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="col-md-8 col-lg-6">
				<div class="login d-flex align-items-center py-5">
					<div class="container">
						<div class="row">

							<!-- login form -->
							<div class="col-md-9 col-lg-8 mx-auto" id="login-block">
								<h3 class="login-heading mb-4">Welcome back!</h3>
								<form>
									<div class="form-label-group">
										<input type="text" id="loginUsername" class="form-control" placeholder="Username" required autofocus>
										<label for="loginUsername">Username</label>
									</div>

									<div class="form-label-group">
										<input type="password" id="loginPassword" class="form-control" placeholder="Password" required>
										<label for="loginPassword">Password</label>
									</div>

									<button class="btn btn-lg btn-primary btn-block btn-login text-uppercase font-weight-bold mb-2" type="submit" id="login">Log in</button>
									<div class="text-center small">
										Don't have account? <a href="#" class="toggle-enter">Create account</a>
									</div>
								</form>
							</div>
						</div>

						<!-- register form -->
						<div class="col-md-9 col-lg-8 mx-auto" id="register-block" style="display: none;">
							<h3 class="login-heading mb-4">Welcome to the club!</h3>
							<form>
								<div class="form-label-group">
									<input type="text" id="registerName" class="form-control" placeholder="Name" required autofocus>
									<label for="registerName">Name</label>
								</div>

								<div class="form-label-group">
									<input type="text" id="registerUsername" class="form-control" placeholder="Username" required autofocus>
									<label for="registerUsername">Username</label>
								</div>

								<div class="form-label-group">
									<input type="password" id="registerPassword" class="form-control" placeholder="Password" required>
									<label for="registerPassword">Password</label>
								</div>

								<button class="btn btn-lg btn-primary btn-block btn-login text-uppercase font-weight-bold mb-2" type="submit" id="signin">Sign in</button>
								<div class="text-center small">
									Already have account? <a href="#" class="toggle-enter">Log in</a>
								</div>
							</form>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>


	<!-- About -->
	<div class="about-sec">
		<div class="container">
			<h1 class="text-center">One Reading Club</h1>
			<h3 class="thin-text text-center">Expanding Our Horizons Together</h3>
			
			<div class="container para">
				<p>Reading makes us smarter, lets us build our own imaginary world, develops critical and analytical thinking, builds vocabulary, improve focus and concentration, expand our horizons and much much more.</p>
				
				<p>But in our busy day schedule with instant satisfaction monkey mind, it’s hard to read and finish books. That’s why at One Reading Club we are developing reading habit as a micro habit.</p>

				<p>What is this micro-habit?</p>

				<p>A micro-habit is simple action that doesn’t require much motivation, but will help you build up to a larger goal habit.</p>

				<p>Our goal is not to read 100 pages a day or read 2 books a month. Our goal is to read everyday.  Initially we start by reading minimum one page a day. Reading one page a day is not a big deal. Right? On average if you will read 2-5 pages, it means a book a month, 12-15 book a year. That’s a lot of book to start with.</p>

				<p>So start and keep reading minimum 1 page a day and update your friends at One Reading Club about that daily. It will keep you motivated and on track.</p>

				<p>Happy reading :)</p>
			</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>

</body>
</html>